  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Kala-azar Control in South Sudan</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The focus of the program includes improved diagnosis and effective treatment, building surveillance capacity and improving the ability to respond to outbreaks.

To meet the overall goal of the program, IMA has embarked on various activities, including training of health workers, establishment of emergency response teams, provision of pharmaceuticals and supplies, re-activation of previous kala-azar treatment centers destroyed during conflict in South Sudan and supporting the Ministry of Health NTD departments.</narrative>
  </description>
